She played Jennifer Kingsley in all seven series of the BBC drama between 1972 and 1976. Her earliest screen roles were Kate Nickleby in the 1957 adaptation of Nicholas Nickleby and DS Helen Webb in the ITV police drama Special Branch, which ran from 1969 to 1974. The recipient of a Rada scholarship, Wilson was in Romeo & Juliet at the Old Vic and was a regular on West End stages including long runs in The Mousetrap. She is survived by her daughter Melanie. JENNIFER WILSON BORN APRIL 25, 1932 - DIED MARCH 29, 2022, AGED 89